SELECT result_id, n, blocks_per_grid, threads_per_block, time_cpu, time_gpu, gflops_cpu, gflops_gpu, power_consumption, temperature, fan_speed
FROM benchmark_results
WHERE time_cpu < (SELECT AVG(time_cpu) FROM benchmark_results);

external_knowledge:
- "shining star" refers to the user who has the highest performance in both aspects of the query; 
- "volume of feedback" is represented by the count of comments (`comment_count`);
- "swiftness of their GPU performance" is indicated by the average GPU time (`average_gpu_time`).

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.user_id, users.username
FROM users
JOIN result_comments ON users.user_id = result_comments.user_id;

SELECT DISTINCT name
FROM gpu_architectures
WHERE clock_speed > 1.5;

external_knowledge:
- "sailors" refers to users who run the benchmarking tests;
- "ships" metaphorically represents the GPU architectures;
- "seas" metaphorically indicates the dates when the tests were run;
- "wind's strength" serves as a metaphor for fan speed in the system;
- "ship's temperature" metaphorically stands for the GPU's temperature;
- "fuel burned" metaphorically represents power consumption during the tests.
